    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1864-09-24T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1864-09-24T00:00:00-05:00" n="205" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d205">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. F. W. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr. Dayton</persName>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 662.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State,</hi>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington,</hi>
                        </placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1864-09-24">
                            <hi rend="italic">September</hi> 24, 1864.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have to acknowledge the receipt of your
                            despatch of the 9th of September, No. 533, in which you inform me that
                            Mr. Drouyn de l’Huys having returned to Paris, you made known to him the
                            views of this government respecting the action of Captain Winslow in
                            releasing the prisoners taken by the Kearsarge. Your proceedings therein
                            indicated are approved.</p>
                <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>F. W. SEWARD. <hi rend="italic">Acting
                            Secretary.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">William L. Dayton,</hi> Esq., <hi rend="italic">&amp;c., &amp;c., &amp;c.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
